				<td colspan="2"><span>I get that a lot LDONing.
<br />

<br />
Muse (melee twist)
<br />
WoZ (melee twist)
<br />
PoV (melee twist)
<br />
CoM (melee twist)
<br />
HoS (for mezz/slow resisters)
<br />
LoM (Mezz)
<br />
RoT(Slow)
<br />
SSoQ(Lull)
<br />

<br />
I pull with bellow, or HoS/ROT combo
<br />

<br />
I have Siren Song and Epic equipped to start, once Siren song Procs I swap in my main weapon for DPS.  Swap in Siren Song whenever proc drops again.
<br />

<br />
That way I have 2 types of Spell haste up at all times, so that when I drop a twist to slow or mezz, the group is still hasted.  There are occasions when both procs drop, usually when there are 2 or more adds.  But that is rare, since I am puller AND cc, I control the amount of adds in camp usually (wanderers suck though!)
<br />

<br />
Using that line up, I rarely need to sit down and mem something else, those 8 songs handle all my duties nicely.
<br />

<br />
If I am doing a hard LDoN, and need to pulse Cha Song before I attempt a lull, I drop HoS
<br />
</span></td>
